  const [width, setWidth] = useState(window.innerWidth);
  // ...
}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Creating Static Versions of Hooks (Good Practice) - React JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates the recommended approach for modifying Hook behavior by creating a new, static version of the Hook with the desired logic inlined. This ensures immutability, promotes local reasoning, and adheres to React's rules for Hooks, allowing for proper optimization.
SOURCE: https://github.com/reactjs/react.dev/blob/main/src/content/reference/rules/react-calls-components-and-hooks.md#_snippet_3

