TITLE: Correctly Passing Immutable Arguments to Hooks
DESCRIPTION: Compares the incorrect practice of mutating a hook's argument after it has been passed to the hook with the correct approach of creating a new object with updated properties. Mutating the original object can lead to the hook returning previously memoized, outdated results, while creating a copy ensures the hook re-calculates values correctly.
