TITLE: Optimizing Custom React Hooks with useCallback
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates the best practice for custom React Hooks: wrapping any functions returned by the hook with `useCallback`. This ensures that consumers of the custom hook receive stable function references across renders, allowing them to optimize their own components and effects that depend on these functions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/reactjs/react.dev/blob/main/src/content/reference/react/useCallback.md#_snippet_23

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
function useRouter() {
  const { dispatch } = useContext(RouterStateContext);

  const navigate = useCallback((url) => {
    dispatch({ type: 'navigate', url });
  }, [dispatch]);

  const goBack = useCallback(() => {
    dispatch({ type: 'back' });
  }, [dispatch]);

  return {
    navigate,
    goBack,
  };
}

```

